What is a Donor Advised Fund?
A donor advised fund is a separately identified fund or account that is maintained and operated by a sponsoring charitable organization. Each account is composed of contributions made by individual donors. Once the donor makes the contribution, the organization has legal control over it. However, the donor retains advisory privileges with respect to the distribution of funds and the investment of assets in the account. Learn more...BNY Mellon Charitable Gift Fund
For those who have achieved success, charitable giving can be a gratifying way to give back. The BNY Mellon Charitable Gift Fund ("the Fund") can provide a structured means to express those philanthropic values and priorities to community as well as family members.
The Fund allows for the establishment of individual donor-advised accounts and was created to manage charitable donations on behalf of donors. Gifting through the Fund can provide simplicity, administrative convenience and flexibility for donors. Furthermore, because the Fund is classified as a public charity by the IRS, donors may be eligible for a tax deduction in the year they make the gift.1 
The Fund is governed by a majority independent Board of Directors. Administration and investment management for the Fund and its underlying accounts are provided through service agreements with BNY Mellon, N.A.21 The Fund is a public charity as described in the Sections of 501(c)(3), 509(a)(1) and 170(b)(1)(A)(vi) of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended, and is eligible to receive tax-deductible charitable contributions under Section 170(c).2 BNY Mellon N.A. makes available investment products to the Fund that are sponsored, distributed, or provided by BNY Mellon, N.A.Charity Search
    
